# Design Tokens

The design system source of truth lives in `docs/design-tokens/`:

- `docs/design-tokens/global.json` — all token values
- `docs/design-tokens/$metadata.json` — token set order
- `docs/design-tokens/$themes.json` — theme configuration

Always read these files before styling UI. Never hardcode colors, font sizes, radii, or spacing.

## Colors

Use semantic groups from `global.json`:

- **Accent** — Primary `#1f4e79`, Secondary `#6283a1`, Tertiary `#8fa6bc`
- **Text** — Primary, Secondary, Accent, Link Hover, Disabled, Inverted
- **Button / Tag / Icon / Border / BG** — component and surface colors
- **Status, Urgency, Feedback, Scoring** — state and semantic colors (background + Text variants)

Map token paths to CSS/Tailwind names (e.g. `Accent.Primary` → `accent-primary`).

## Typography

**Font families:** IBM Plex Sans (headings), Source Sans 3 (body, UI, meta).

**Font sizes (px):** 12, 14, 16, 18, 24, 28, 32.

**Desktop styles** — use the named presets in `global.json`:

| Category | Styles |
|----------|--------|
| Header | H1, H2, H3 |
| Body | Eyebrow 1/2, Paragraph, Table |
| UI | Button, Navigation, Tooltip, Status badge, Filter & input label |
| Meta | Tender title, Small text, Caption |

Each preset defines fontFamily, fontWeight, lineHeight, fontSize, letterSpacing, and textCase. Match these exactly.

## Spacing

Spacing tokens are not defined in JSON. Use a **4px base grid**: 4, 8, 12, 16, 20, 24, 32, 40, 48, etc. Never use arbitrary values (e.g. 13px, 22px).

## Radii

- **Containers:** `4px` (`Containers` token in `global.json`)

## Shadows

Shadow tokens are not defined in JSON. Prefer **thin borders** (`Border.Light` `#e5e8ec`, `Border.Dark` `#d9d9d9`) over box shadows. Avoid decorative or heavy elevation.

## Rules

- Never introduce colors, type, spacing, radii, or shadows outside this system.
- When a value is missing from the token files, ask before inventing one.
- Status/urgency UI must use the paired background + text color tokens.
